373
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:18,913
We're havin' some decent friends over.

374
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:23,790
What Ed means to say is...

375
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:27,917
seein' as you two boys are wanted,

376
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:34,949
it wouldn't exactly do to have folks seein'
you here. It's for your own protection.

377
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:37,998
- Sure, H I.
- Anything you say, Hi.

378
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:42,953
Matter of fact, honey,
I think I'll skip this little get-together myself.

379
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:47,591
Glen won't mind. I'll just duck out with
the boys, knock back a coupla co-colas.

380
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:51,193
- Sure, H I.
- We'd love to have you, Hi.

381
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:58,276
Maybe that ain't such a swell idea, either.

382
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:04,709
So many social engagements,

383
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,951
so little time.

384
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,639
Where's that baby? Where is he at?

385
00:34:18,720 --> 00:34:21,757
- Go find him, honey!
- Cut it out, Glen!

386
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:23,831
He's asleep right now.

387
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:25,956
Shit! I hope we didn't wake it!

388
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:28,634
Can I just sneak a peek-a-loo?

389
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:32,715
Come on, kids!
Get away from Mr McDunnough's car!

390
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:42,235
What's his name?

391
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:46,999
Hi... Hi Junior, till we think of a better one.

392
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:50,479
Why don't ya call him Jason?
I love biblical names.

393
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:53,552
If I had another little boy,
I'd name him Jason, Caleb or Tab.

394
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:58,115
He's an angel!
He's an angel straight from heaven!

395
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:00,316
Now honey, I had all my kids the hard way.

396
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:04,313
Tell me how you got this little angel.
