01:24:14,400 --> 01:24:20,430
<i>I dreamt that Gale and Evelle had decided to
return to prison. Probably that's just as well.</i>

886
01:24:20,520 --> 01:24:25,310
<i>I don't mean to sound superior,
and they're a swell coupla guys,</i>

887
01:24:26,040 --> 01:24:30,113
<i>but maybe they weren't ready yet
to come out into the world.</i>

888
01:24:31,720 --> 01:24:35,508
<i>And then I dreamed on, into the future,</i>

889
01:24:36,720 --> 01:24:42,829
<i>to a Christmas morning in the Arizona home,
where Nathan Junior was openin'a present</i>

890
01:24:42,920 --> 01:24:46,913
<i>from a kindly couple
who preferred to remain unknown.</i>

891
01:24:49,360 --> 01:24:52,193
<i>I saw Glen a few years later,</i>

892
01:24:52,280 --> 01:24:57,354
<i>still havin'no luck gettin' the cops
to listen to his wild tales about me and Ed.</i>

893
01:24:59,480 --> 01:25:02,313
<i>Maybe he threw in one Polack joke too many.</i>

894
01:25:03,360 --> 01:25:04,839
<i>I don't know.</i>

895
01:25:06,840 --> 01:25:08,990
<i>But still I dreamed on,</i>

896
01:25:09,840 --> 01:25:13,799
<i>further into the future
than I'd ever dreamed before.</i>

897
01:25:15,040 --> 01:25:18,237
<i>Watchin' Nathan Junior's progress from afar,</i>

898
01:25:19,320 --> 01:25:24,155
<i>takin' pride in his accomplishments,
as if he were our own,</i>

899
01:25:25,440 --> 01:25:28,318
<i>wonderin' if he ever thought of us,</i>

900
01:25:29,360 --> 01:25:33,831
<i>and hopin' that maybe we'd
broadened his horizons a little,</i>

901
01:25:33,920 --> 01:25:38,072
<i>even if he couldn't remember
just how they got broadened.</i>

902
01:25:39,680 --> 01:25:43,798
<i>But still I hadn't dreamt
nothin' about me and Ed,</i>

903
01:25:43,880 --> 01:25:45,871
<i>until the end.</i>

904
01:25:46,720 --> 01:25:49,075
<i>And this was cloudier,</i>

905
01:25:49,160 --> 01:25:52,948
<i>because it was years, years away.</i>

906
01:25:55,240 --> 01:25:59,552
<i>But I saw an old couple
bein' visited by their children</i>

907
01:25:59,640 --> 01:26:02,279
<i>and all their grandchildren too.</i>

908
01:26:03,200 --> 01:26:09,196
<i>The old couple weren't screwed up,
and neither were their kids or their grandkids.</i>

909
01:26:09,920 --> 01:26:11,478
Dad...

910
01:26:11,560 --> 01:26:13,551
<i>And I don't know.</i>

911
01:26:14,280 --> 01:26:16,157
<i>You tell me.</i>

912
01:26:16,240 --> 01:26:18,231
<i>This whole dream.</i>

913
01:26:19,240 --> 01:26:21,231
<i>Was it wishful thinkin'?</i>

914
01:26:21,920 --> 01:26:26,914
<i>Was I just fleein'reality,
like I know I'm liable to do?</i>

915
01:26:28,400 --> 01:26:32,712
<i>But me and Ed, we can be good too.</i>

916
01:26:34,320 --> 01:26:36,311
<i>And it seemed real.</i>

917
01:26:37,760 --> 01:26:39,751
<i>It seemed like us.</i>

918
01:26:40,240 --> 01:26:42,231
<i>And it seemed like,</i>

919
01:26:42,960 --> 01:26:45,349
<i>well... our home.</i>

920
01:26:47,480 --> 01:26:51,871
<i>If not Arizona, then a land not too far away,</i>

921
01:26:53,400 --> 01:26:57,188
<i>where all parents are
strong and wise and capable</i>

922
01:26:58,480 --> 01:27:01,677
<i>and all the children are happy and beloved.</i>

923
01:27:03,360 --> 01:27:05,351
<i>I don't know.</i>

924
01:27:07,000 --> 01:27:09,195
<i>Maybe it was Utah.</i>

925
01:29:44,760 --> 01:29:49,675
